        {
            "block_label": "text",
            "block_content": "Risk-Based Regulatory Capital. Risk-based capital ratio requirements apply to Common Equity Tier 1 (\"CET1\") capital, Tier 1 capital and Total capital (which includes Tier 2 capital), each as a percentage of RWA, and consist of regulatory minimum required ratios plus the Firm's capital conservation buffer requirement. Capital requirements require certain adjustments to, and deductions from, capital for purposes of determining these ratios. At March 31, 2026 and December 31, 2025, the differences between the actual and required ratios were lower under the Standardized Approach.",
