        {
            "block_label": "text",
            "block_content": "The capital conservation buffer requirement represents the amount of CET1 capital the Firm must maintain above the minimum risk-based capital requirements in order to avoid restrictions on the Firm's ability to make capital distributions, including the payment of dividends and the repurchase of stock, and to pay discretionary bonuses to executive officers. The Firm's capital conservation buffer requirement computed under the standardized approaches for calculating credit risk and market risk RWA (\"Standardized Approach\") is equal to the sum of the SCB, G-SIB capital surcharge and CCyB. The capital conservation buffer requirement computed under the applicable advanced approaches for calculating credit risk, market risk and operational risk RWA (\"Advanced Approach\") is equal to the sum of a fixed 2.5% buffer, G-SIB capital surcharge and CCyB.",
